channel.title: New Java Question
channel.description: Hello, Since a few days i was wondering why you see strange symbols when opening a file in my scrapbook. Once i've found the reason i started to try opening files in Java. Also known as: 'Java Web Start Launcher'. But the problem is the second, once i'm trying to open a file i get the second error: 'Unable to launch the application.'. In this area i have 2 options; Details or cancel.. And once i'm clicking on Details i can see all the information what is in the file i'm trying to open. Including 2 more tabs which are 'Exception' and 'Wrapped Exception'. Any idea's how to fix this? Greetings, Z2

item.description:
@Zandstorm2 wrote:

Hello,
Since a few days i was wondering why you see strange symbols when opening a file in my scrapbook.
Once i’ve found the reason i started to try opening files in Java. Also known as: ‘Java Web Start Launcher’.
But the problem is the second, once i’m trying to open a file i get the second error: ‘Unable to launch the application.’.
In this area i have 2 options; Details or cancel… And once i’m clicking on Details i can see all the information what is in the file i’m trying to open. Including 2 more tabs which are ‘Exception’ and ‘Wrapped Exception’.
Any idea’s how to fix this?
Greetings,
Z2
